&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and dedicated individual to join the Obstetrics and Gynaecology team at the West Middlesex Site of the Chelsea and Westminster Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We wish to appoint a suitably trained and experienced doctor with NHS experience at ST6 -7 level as a Senior Clinical Fellow to work as a Senior Registrar with a special interest in Acute Gynaecology &amp; Early Pregnancy or Maternal Medicine and Obstetric Research. The post will provide specialised training towards the completion of the Maternal Medicine ATSM. The successful candidate will also be expected to contribute to the SpR on call Rota and will be provided with an Educational Supervisor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited to apply as soon as possible with a proposed start date in October 2020. The successful candidate should be registered with the GMC and should have relevant NHS experience to work at the level of ST6 -7 within a busy Obstetrics and Gynaecology unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;interview &lt;/strong&gt;will be held on the &lt;strong&gt;20th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;. It is expected that the interviews will be conducted virtually either on Zoom or Microsoft Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Mr Osakwe - Consultant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Osaeloke.Osakwe@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
